    "comment": "Rationale: In both figures 1 and 3, the authors used synaptic vesicle proteins tagged with pH sensitive pHlourins to monitor synaptic vesicle endocytosis. The fluorescence of synapses expressing the pHlourin tagged proteins were measured in rat hippocampal neurons in culture. siRNAs targeting stonin 2 were used to knockdown the protein. The neurons were stimulated with 40 APs at 20 Hz and then allowed to recover, with the decay of the pHlourin signal a measure of endocytosis. Stonin 2 knockdown reduces endocytosis using multiple pHlourins.. Experimental description: From the supplemental experimental procedures, \"Primary cultures of rat hippocampal neurons were prepared from E19 rat pups...\"",
